main event: An object was observed traveling from Toledo, Ohio to Lake Erie at a high rate of speed for 45 minutes.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be traveling at about 600 knots,The sighting involved ground visual and ground radar observations,Possible explanations for the sighting included balloon, helicopter, aircraft, and astronomical phenomena,Another report suggested the object traveled from Toledo, Ohio to Selfridge AFB, Michigan in one minute at a speed estimated at 4,500 knots,The size, shape, or color of the object could not be determined.
